pt-br.purpose: Possibilita que o conteúdo clínico de um arquétipo CLUSTER existente seja representado como um dado independente em um registro de saúde.
pt-br.use:
Permite que o conteúdo de um arquétipo CLUSTER existente e geralmente representado dentro do contéudo de outros arquétipos seja representado como dado independente em um registro de saúde quando clinicamente apropriado.

Este arquétipo deve ser utilizado apenas como um arquétipo container para flexibilizar o uso de um arquétipo CLUSTER existente. Ele não se destina a ser usado para representar qualquer conteúdo que não venha via seu SLOT irrestrito.

Por exemplo, o arquétipo CLUSTER.nyha_heart_failure é geralmente usado para fornecer uma avaliação padronizada sobre insuficiência cardíaca com o arquétipo EVALUATION.problem_diagnosis, mas inserindo-o dentro de EVALUATION possiblita-se que ele seja registrado como dados fora do contexto de um Diagnóstico, se clinicamente apropriado. Da mesma forma, CLUSTER.tos é geralmente registrado por otorrinolaringologistas no contexto de um exame usando CLUSTER.exam_tympanic_membrane, mas inserindo-o neste arquétipo, possibilita-se que ele seja registrado fora do contexto dos achados clinicos, se clinicamente apropriado.
pt-br.misuse: Não deve ser usado para representar conteúdo clínico específico definido dentro deste arquétipo.

en.purpose: To enable the clinical content held within existing CLUSTER archetypes to be represented as standalone data in the health record.
en.use:
Use to enable the clinical content held within existing CLUSTER archetypes, and usually represented within the context of other archetypes, to be represented as standalone data in the health record when clinically appropriate. 

This archetype is intended only to act as a container archetype that supports flexible expression of existing CLUSTER archetypes. It is not intended to hold any content other than the unconstrained SLOT.

For example, the CLUSTER.nyha_heart_failure archetype is most commonly used to provide a standardised assessment of heart failure with EVALUATION.problem_diagnosis archetypes, but by inserting it within this EVALUATION allows it to be recorded as data outside the context of a Diagnosis, if clinically appropriate. Similarly CLUSTER.tos is usually recorded by ENT specialists in the context of an examination using CLUSTER.exam_tympanic_membrane, but by inserting it into this archetype, it allows it to be recorded outside the context of examination findings, if clinically appropriate.
en.misuse: Not to be used to represent specific clinical content defined within this archetype.

author.name: Gabriela Alves, Adriana Kitajima, Marivan Abrahao, Maria Angela Scatena

de.purpose: Bereitstellung einer systematischen Einteilung zur Erfassung aller unerwünschten und unerwarteten Ereignissen, Symptome oder Krankheiten unter Verwendung der CTCAE-Terminologie.
de.use:
*A framework for recording any unfavourable and unintended sign, symptom or disease temporally associated with the use of a medical treatment or procedure that may or may not be considered related to the medical treatment or procedure using the CTCAE terminology.

This archetype is intended to be used within the context of the CLUSTER.symptom_sign, EVALUATION.problem_diagnosis, OBSERVATION.symptom_sign_screening archetype or other clinically relevant archetypes.

The 'Term' field is intended to be populated using a coded text based on 'CTCAE term' coded with 'MedDRA Code' terms only.

In a template or at runtime populate the 'Grade' ordinal field with e.g. applicable values  and descriptions from the 'Grade 1' ... 'Grade 5' columns of the CTCAE spreadsheet. (en)
de.misuse: *When querying data for severity level, please refer to the DV_ORDINAL.value field, do NOT select data based on the symbol/name or "at-code" of the archetype value, since these may change in different templates or translations. (en)

sv.purpose: Ett ramverk för att med hjälp av CTCAE-terminologin registrera eventuella biverkningar eller ogynnsamma och oavsiktliga symptom eller sjukdomar.
sv.use:
Ett ramverk för att registrera biverkningar och andra ogynnsamma och oavsiktliga symtom eller sjukdomar som är tidsmässigt förknippade med användningen av en medicinsk behandling eller procedur som kan eller inte kan anses relaterad till den medicinska behandlingen eller proceduren med användning av CTCAE-terminologin.

Denna arketyp är avsedd att användas inom ramen för arketypen CLUSTER.symptom_sign, EVALUATION.problem_diagnosis,  OBSERVATION.symptom_sign_screening eller andra kliniskt relevanta arketyper.

"Term"-fältet är avsett att fyllas i med en kodad text baserad på "CTCAE term" kodad med "MedDRA Code"-termer.

I en mall eller applikation ska man i  fältet "allvarlighetsgrad" ange tillämpliga värden och beskrivningar från kolumnerna 'Grade 1' ... 'Grade 5' i CTCAE-kalkylarket.

För svensk kontext se t.ex. https://healthcaredelivery.cancer.gov/pro-ctcae/pro-ctcae_swedish.pdf och https://healthcaredelivery.cancer.gov/pro-ctcae/pro-ctcae_swedish.pdf
sv.misuse: När sökningar avseende allvarlighetsgrad görs, basera dem då på fältet DV_ORDINAL.value, basera inte sökningen på symbol/name eller "at-kod" eftersom dessa kan variera i olika templates eller översättningar.
